*** The Basic Kubernetes Commands ***

How can we count number of pods in a namespace ?
#kubectl get pods -n "yournamespacename"
#kubectl get pods -n myspace

How can we create a pod , given base image is nginx ?
#kubectl run "yourpodname" --image="baseimagename" 
#kubectl run myimage --image=nginx 

How do we need know details of a specific pod ?
#kubectl describe pod "yourpodname" -n "yournamespacename"
#kubectl describe pod myimage -n myspace 
-- look for the container row 

How do we know which node that pods are placed on ?
#kubectl get pods -n "yournamespacename" -o wide 
#kubectl get pods -n myspace -o wide 

How many containers are part of your pod , Their states & what are the images that they are running on?
#kubectl describe pod "yourpodname" -n "yournamespacename"
#kubectl describe pod myimage -n myspace 
--look at the containers rows 

How can we delete a pod ? 
#kubectl delete pod "mypodname" -n "mynamespacename"
#kubectl delete pod "myimage" -n "myspace" 

Create a new pod with the YAML File ?
#kubectl run "yourpodname" --image="yourbaseimagename" --dry-run=client -o yaml > "yourfilename".yaml 
#kubectl run "myimage2" --image=redis --dry-run=client -o yaml > redis.yaml


*** The Replicaset Commands ***

Creating a Replicaset using the Replicaset Definition YAML File 
#kubectl create -f "Your Replicaset YAML File Name"
#kubectl create -f rc-definition.yml 

To see the Replicasets 
#kubectl get replicaset

To see the Pods created by the Replicaset
#kubectl get pods

To delete the Replicaset 
#kubectl delete replicaset "replicasetname"
#kubectl delete replicaset my-replicaset 

For editing the Replicaset
In this commnds we can use replicaset or rs , both are same 
#kubectl edit rs "my replicaset name"
#kubectl edit rs my-rcset 

For scaling purpose , means for incresing or decresing the replicas count 
We can edit the Replicaset definition File & run the below command 
#kubectl replace -f "replicaset_definition YAML File"
#kubectl replace -f myreplicaset-definition.YML

Without editing the defintion file 
#kubectl scale -replicas="any number that you need" -f "your definition YAML File"
#kubectl scale -replicas=6 -f myreplicaset-definition.YML
or by running the scale on replicaset itself
#kubectl scale rs "your replicaset name" --replicas="the number that you need"
#kubectl scale rs my-replicaset --replicas=5


*** The Deployments Commands ***

For creating the deployment from the Definition File 
#kubectl create -f "Your deployment  YAML File Name"
#kubectl create -f my-deployment.yml

For getting the deployments listed 
#kubectl get deployment

For getting all the obejects
#kubectl get all









